description: In "Over the Hill," an insurmountable hill is the source of Archie's ills in this snow-filled tale! Archie attempts something harder than splitting the atom,  trying to get his best girl Veronica and his best buddy Jughead to get along with each other in "Just a Perfect Friendship." And in "My Boy Juggie," Betty and Veronica are worried that Archie will go girl crazy on a solo trip to the ski lodge so they convince Jughead to go with him. Everyone run for cover, Jinx Malloy is on the move in "The Jinx is Back!"
name: Over The Hill; Just A Perfect Friendship; My Boy Juggie; The Jinx Is Back;

description: Solitaire joins in the fight for corporate supremacy!  The Night Man and Prototype guest star.  While all this is happening, Anton Lone makes plans of his own.  He makes a bold move to seize control over all the ultra-creating technology known to exist.  This all builds up to the final conflict between Solitaire and Anton Lone, the father he wishes he never had.  Cover by Scott Kolins and Jon Holdredge.
name: Hostile Takeover (Part 2): Hole In The Head

description: The hit comic based on the game concludes! Biological weapons, unhinged commandos, violent creatures and more round out this final issue! New York City stands as a symbol of our nation, but if New York homicide detectives can't rise to the occasion and stop events that are in play, NYC will become a wasteland.

The main feature this month focuses on the DC Universe's bizarre answer to Thelma & Louise as Black Canary and her rival Cupid end up on the lam from both Big Game and the Star City Police! Meanwhile, this issue's co-feature sees Green Arrow doing his best to bring down Big Game himself before the baddie can find either woman in GA's life!
name: Big Game: We, Prey

description: IDW's newly recolored reprints of classic Doctor Who tales from years past continues. In this issue, the adventures of the Fifth Doctor continues in 'Lunar Lagoon' and Part 1 of '4-Dimensional Vistas.'

IDW's newly recolored reprints of classic Doctor Who tales from years past continues. In this issue, the final three chapters of the classic tale, 'The Stockbridge Horror,' starring the Fifth Doctor, by Steve Parkhouse. Featuring all-new colors by Charlie Kirchoff.

Vincent Price tells another gothic adventure. In 'Fade Away,' Private Eye Frank Wood takes on a case in which he must investigate mysterious break-ins at a home belonging to a wealthy old man named Jack Leonard. Is there really an intruder or is Jack losing his mind and seeing someone that isn't there?
name: Fade Away

description: Meriem, Bruce, Prof. Cook, and Kylde are on trip to a newly discovered tar pit. While there, they run into an absolutely humongous savaging mass of furious fire eating ants! Marshville seems to be directly in their way and Meriem and crew better do something to save their friends from being torn apart, but what can be done against the threat of the red menace?

description: This September, the Hunter becomes the Hunted as Image and Liar Comics spin a haunting tale featuring Morand, the Witchfinder, from the popular More Than Mortal comic. The brash young priest teams up with the infamous Matthew Hopkins, the Witchfinder General of England, to hunt down and punish a group of Irish heretics. In this first exciting issue, Hopkins is revealed as a sadistic power monger, and Morand must face his biggest test. The young priest will find himself caught between the terrible dark secret that brands him a witch, and his desire to take revenge on the heretics for the death of his brother. Sometimes, a man's need for vengeance can consume him.

Things go from bad to worse, as young Morand's terrible secret is revealed! The townspeople turn on him, and he must join forces with another witch in order to stay alive. Things heat up as his nemesis, Matthew Hopkins, uses every device at his disposal to set an insidious trap for the young priest. Can Morand escape the cunning plan and prove his innocence before they burn him at the stake?

December marks the awesome finale to Liar Comic's dark tale of revenge and redemption, as The Witchfinder comes to terms with his torturous past. The life of Brin, an innocent girl, hangs in the balance, when Morand and his new mentor attempt to free her from Hopkin's maniacal grasp. Can he make his way in and out of the fire once more?
